nknown","label":"Longest daily candle since breakout","evidence":"No completed model breakout history.","value":null}],"positiveNewsNegativeReaction":{"status":"unknown","label":"Positive news with negative price action","evidence":"No verified news-reaction evidence supplied.","value":null}},"notes":["Technical stop is wider than 10%; this model entry is not feasible and no position size is suggested.","Verified earnings date unavailable; earnings risk remains Unknown."]},"mentions":[{"mentioned_at":"2026-07-16T15:57:05.000Z","text":"Serenity guessed semis may be close to a market bottom, mentioning $INTC, $LITE, and $RDDT.","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2077784594959725056"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-19T09:04:06.000Z","text":"Serenity @aleabitoreddit · 4h Bernstein is basically the institutional version of Jim Cramer: Tells retail Kioxia looks like it’s going to crash, gives a -50% PT. Bunch of retail sells. Stock proceeds to skyrocket right after, with another +12% today. Quote Serenity @aleabitoreddit · Jun 17 Bernstein is legit the dumbest analyst firm I’ve seen calling for a 50% crash in Kioxia. They gave $INTC a $36 PT back in Jan and now it’s $118. Good lesson to ignore institutional reports that get published for retail consumption. They’re not here to help retail investors. x.com/bloombergjapan… 104 63 880 221K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2067896191338311750"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-18T15:06:08.000Z","text":"Serenity @aleabitoreddit · 22h Trump announced Intel + Apple partnership, sending $INTC up 8% today. Intel execs were reportedly surprised by the $AAPL announcement by Donald Trump. TBH, the President should lead Intel's marketing team at this point. Feel's like he's hard carrying the stock. 197 73 1.2K 279K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2067624913834549685"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-17T05:31:46.000Z","text":"Serenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\n18h\nBernstein is legit the dumbest analyst firm I’ve seen calling for a 50% crash in Kioxia.\n\nThey gave \n$INTC\n a $36 PT back in Jan and now it’s $118.\n\nGood lesson to ignore institutional reports that get published for retail consumption. \n\nThey’re not here to help retail investors.\nQuote\nブルームバーグニュース\n@BloombergJapan\n·\n21h\nTranslated from Japanese\nKioxia, the top market cap company, has 50% downside potential in its stock price - Bernstein \nhttps://\nbloomberg.com/jp/news/articl\nes/2026-06-16/TGPT24KJH6V600?taid=6a31fc52fbb36b0001befef1&utm_campaign=trueanthem&utm_content=japan&utm_medium=social&utm_source=twitter\n…\n121\n80\n1.5K\n442K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2067117980656533764"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-16T07:54:44.000Z","text":"Serenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\n6h\nI did say \n$MU\n looked like the next \n$NVDA\n. Now we're at a $1.23T MC.\n\nStarted talking more about Samsung Electronics/Sk Hynix back in 2025. \n\nPut more concentration into the memory theme like \n$SNDK\n and others, Jan of this year. \n\nAnd I'm glad my prediction with Micron + memory is\nShow more\nQuote\nSerenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\nJan 22\n$MU looks like the next Nvidia. \n\nWhen Nvidia was $400B (now $4.5T+), markets thought GPUs were a short-term cycle.\n\nSame with memory today. \n\nAI has broken that cycle.\n\nWith the same \"Made in America\" and White House backing like $INTC:\n\nDon't overthink things with Micron.  x.com/aleabitoreddit…\n239\n99\n100\n1.5K\n433K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2066791570569916832"}],"topDownContext":{"alignment":"Unknown","chains":[]}},{"symbol":"COHR","mention_count":3,"first_mention":"2026-06-18T09:38:11.000Z","latest_mention":"2026-07-13T19:20:46.000Z","mentions_24h":0,"tweets_24h":0,"prices":[{"date":"2025-02-28","open":74,"high":76.16999816894531,"low":72.58000183105469,"close":75.19000244140625,"volume":3617100},{"date":"2025-03-03",