s $NBIS and $IREN. Source noted: NYT.","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2078175882620059719"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-07-14T14:57:21.000Z","text":"$$NBIS signs $1B+ compute agreement with Reflection AI, for GB300 access through 2029. Reflection also signed a multi-billion dollar agreement with $SPCX earlier. Interesting to see Nebius drop -5% off the news today.","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2077044786402660829"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-07-13T00:45:13.000Z","text":"Serenity @aleabitoreddit · 1h Just a semi recap TLDR: - $GLW glass bridge per Morgan Stanley has potential, but hard to displace FAU (like FOCI) in short term - $SPCX Starlink Gen 3 is scaling to 100,000 units (10x prev gen) creating possible capacity constraints for suppliers of switches to CCL. - PCB Show more 111 112 47 637 640 120K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2076467953995071881"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-18T13:45:08.000Z","text":"Serenity @aleabitoreddit · 23h I think Jim Cramer’s law needs to be studied in history books. Even $SPCX can’t withstand his blessing. Quote Serenity @aleabitoreddit · Jun 17 Jim Cramer gave $SPCX his blessing. x.com/jimcramer/stat… 258 96 1.7K 464K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2067604528959238272"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-17T15:46:21.000Z","text":"Serenity @aleabitoreddit · 22h Jim Cramer gave $SPCX his blessing. Quote Jim Cramer @jimcramer · Jun 17 I clock SpaceX going up one point per hour 221 150 1.7K 567K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2067272647545930045"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-16T11:01:48.000Z","text":"Serenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\n3h\nWoah, \n$SPCX\n acquired Cursor for $60B.\n\nI did not think it was worth that much…\n\nMaybe network effect or data for improving models became invaluable? \n\nI’m sure Elon has a plan in mind, the Twitter acquisition paid extreme dividends.\n242\n80\n941\n169K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2066838650193949091"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-16T00:19:25.000Z","text":"Serenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\n14h\nApparently, \n$SPCX\n is a $2.5T company now. \n\nI did say Americans would buy anything futuristic without caring about valuations... \n\nI guess everything in Murica go brrr.\nQuote\nSerenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\nJun 14\nIf I had to stereotype my X experiences with markets:\n\nChina : set on cloning me with AI, can only think of trades in short term timeframes from A-shares PTSD.\n\nAmerica :  bullish on anything futuristic like $SPCX, don’t care about valuations\n\nEurope : from $SIVE to $SOI,\n335\n96\n1.7K\n623K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2066676986324648239"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-14T15:27:22.000Z","text":"Serenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\n5h\nThis is gonna upset a lot of people: \n\nBut TA is astrology for traders.\n\nIt's confirmation bias + trading human psychology about entries. \n\nKinda like how people frontran \n$SPCE\n from \n$SPCX\n IPO expecting retail to mess up tickers by trading psychology. \n\n$SIVE didn't go up 1900%\nShow more\nQuote\nMax Williamson\n@max_williamson\n·\nJun 13\nReplying to @aleabitoreddit\nDo you use TA at all or are you 100% bottle neck research?\n465\n152\n1.7K\n344K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2066180704661356593"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-13T22:51:12.000Z","text":"Serenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\n33m\nIf I had to stereotype my X experiences with markets:\n\nChina : set on cloning me with AI, can only think of trades in short term timeframes from A-shares PTSD.\n\nAmerica :  bullish on anything futuristic like \n$SPCX\n, don’t care about valuations\n\nEurope : from $SIVE to $SOI,\nShow more\n227\n34\n438\n30K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2065930011023204509"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-12T15:55:15.000Z"