plan","availability":"available","disclaimer":"Public educational model plan only; not an actual holding, live alert or order.","assumptions":{"entryAtPivot":true,"maxRiskUsd":250,"defaultBuyMethod":"end_of_day"},"feasible":false,"entryPrice":196.5,"initialStop":110.5,"supportEvidence":"Most recent local low on 2026-07-08.","stopDistancePct":43.77,"riskPerShare":86,"quantitySuggested":null,"plannedMaxLossUsd":null,"targets":{"oneR":282.5,"twoR":368.5,"threeR":454.5,"partialExitAllocation":"unknown"},"monitoring":{"asOf":"2026-07-20","dailyCloseOnly":true,"ma20":127.35,"lowerLows":[160.87,127.01,110.5]},"stageMaturity":{"status":"unknown","baseCount":null,"evidence":"No verified early/late-stage evidence supplied."},"sellIntoWeakness":{"courseUse":"Early Stage 2: allow normal pullbacks and sell when weakness is actually observed.","signals":[{"status":"pass","label":"Close below 20MA","evidence":"Latest close is below 20MA.","value":true},{"status":"pass","label":"Three lower lows","evidence":"Three descending local lows observed.","value":true},{"status":"pass","label":"Initial stop / support breach","evidence":"Latest daily low reached the model stop.","value":null},{"status":"unknown","label":"Price and volume deterioration","evidence":"The lesson gives no fixed threshold; review the displayed OHLCV evidence manually.","value":null},{"status":"unknown","label":"Earnings risk","evidence":"Verified earnings date unavailable.","value":null}]},"sellIntoStrength":{"courseUse":"Late-stage market or stock: consider realizing gains into strength and resistance.","levels":{"oneR":282.5,"twoR":368.5,"threeR":454.5,"chartResistance":"unknown"},"climaxSignals":[{"status":"fail","label":"Correction volume exceeds every post-breakout day","evidence":"This signal is not present in the latest session.","value":false},{"status":"unknown","label":"Unusually high volume without matching price progress","evidence":"No verified event/chart judgement supplied.","value":null},{"status":"fail","label":"Longest daily candle since breakout","evidence":"Latest candle is not the widest since breakout.","value":false}],"positiveNewsNegativeReaction":{"status":"unknown","label":"Positive news with negative price action","evidence":"No verified news-reaction evidence supplied.","value":null}},"notes":["Technical stop is wider than 10%; this model entry is not feasible and no position size is suggested.","Verified earnings date unavailable; earnings risk remains Unknown."]},"mentions":[{"mentioned_at":"2026-07-17T16:11:12.000Z","text":"The post discusses a personal $AAOI thesis tied to a potential quarterly revenue ramp to $1.4B in Q3 2027 and asks whether the thesis is invalid before that ramp appears.","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2078150537074373117"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-07-17T14:52:40.000Z","text":"Serenity discussed $AAOI and a personal thesis around possible Q3 2027 revenue ramp assumptions.","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2078130772121399553"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-07-14T14:35:50.000Z","text":"Two different capacity expansion announcements today across $TSEM and $AAOI. Tower Semi announced expansion of 300mm Silicon Photonics, Silicon Germanium, and advanced packaging capabilities.","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2077039373711970804"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-22T14:19:34.000Z","text":"Serenity @aleabitoreddit · 16m That’s for you to decide. But just throwing this out there: If $AAOI hits projections, that’s over 800%+ Y/Y growth, and $5.6B revenue annualized off $12.8B MC. My guess is that the $471m/month will keep going up as demand seems to scale exponentially into 2028. I’d expect Show more Quote l000h @l000h110096 · 2h Replying to @aleabitoreddit What price do you think is appropriate to buy $AAOI? 64 13 299 81K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2069062745308254434"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-21T07:53:18.000Z","text":"Serenity @aleabitoreddit · 15h I've been getting a lot of questions about OE Solutions (138080) recently. Here's my research/thoughts so far on it: They're a small Korean optical transceiver company, similar to $AAOI . And they've become one the few EML players in the world (eg. $COHR , $LITE , Mitsubishi, Show more Quote The Unintelligent Investor @unintellignt · Jun 16 Replying to @aleabitoreddit Optoelectronics 138080 173 81 921 422K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2068603148311404902"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-18T09:38:11.000Z","text":"Serenity @aleabitoreddit · 4h 非常感谢中文社区对我最看好股票的投资思路进行的深度剖析！ 总的来说，像 $AAOI 和 $SIVE 这样的激光公司是我个人的最爱，因为它们在拓展营收方面有着极大的想象空间。它们可以不仅仅局限于销售激光器，还能制造完整的光模块 以及各种光引擎或 ELS (外部光源) 组件。 又或者像 $COHR Show more Quote 梭哈.AI @SUOHA_AI · Jun 17 Article Serenity 从 $28 喊到 $195 的美股标的：$AAOI 到底强在哪里？ 看完这篇文章，你可以完全理解 Serenity 为什么会反复看好 $AAOI ，股价一路上涨，但她却越涨越加仓...于是我把Serenity 关于 $AAOI 的 33 条推文重新研究了一遍... 315 112 1.5K 329K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2067542382523122001"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-17T15:24:06.000Z","text":"Serenity @aleabitoreddit · 22h $AEHR receives follow up production order from major Silicon Photonics Customer for wafer level burn in systems. Now up 11.29% today to $116. Only 2 months ago it was in the $30's, good times. Quote Serenity @aleabitoreddit · Apr 2 $AEHR looks extremely promising at ~$1.1B MC. Aehr is starting to remind me of an early $TER, mixed with pre-earnings $AAOI. If we look at the timeline and speculated customers: Feb 11th: Sonoma production win for Hyperscaler's AI ASIC processors. (likely $GOOGL, $AMZN, 114 146 1.2K 409K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2067267047781015579"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-17T11:24:26.000Z","text":"Serenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\n12h\nTrendforce reports that \n$AMD\n is actively trying to secure CW laser supply with multiple major procurement orders...\n\nIs probably just the start of the bottleneck?  \n\nThere's not much independent capacity in Western supply chains left other than $SIVE or \n$AAOI\n and maybe Macom.\nShow more\n140\n111\n1.3K\n265K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2067206734427697196"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-17T02:26:55.000Z","text":"Serenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\n21h\nI’m not sure why many folks are super bearish on my high conviction \n$AAOI\n long… \n\nEver since $30, then on the way up to $170. (Yes I do think every bear is wrong, we’ll see who’s right).\n\nThey have scarce laser capacity that \n$AMD\n and other hyperscalers are looking for.\n\nWhile\nShow more\nQuote\nAMITESHKUMAR\n@Amiteshkumar840\n·\n22h\nReplying to @aleabitoreddit\nAAOI又高跳下落，对此你怎么看\n192\n130\n1.7K\n730K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2067071462360666165"},{"mentioned_at":"2026-06-16T07:28:51.000Z","text":"Serenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\n7h\nFun throwback to random ideas back in 2025.\n\nBack then, \n$AAOI\n was $2B MC, \n$LITE\n was a $26B MC, \n$AXTI\n was $500M\n\nNow:\n- AAOI is $15.37B\n- Lumentum is $74.47B\n- AXT is $7.24B\n\nWas working off less information back then, given it was an early theme. \n\nObviously nuances with ASIC\nShow more\nQuote\nSerenity\n@aleabitoreddit\n·\nDec 22, 2025\nReplying to @manukafirth\n\"Late\". \n\n$LITE is a $26B MC in the center of every future $GOOGL TPU deployment, $NVDA/ $AMZN / other GPU/ASICs. \n\n8-12% BOM share of every Google TPU v7. This is like saying $NVDA was \"late\" when price it was a $1T MC.\n\nBut if you want want another player, $AAOI. \n\n$MSFT is\n187\n53\n933\n291K","source":"browser_visible","url":"https://x.com/aleabitoreddit/status/2066785056031670657"}],"topDownContext":{"alignment":"Unknown","chains":[]}},{"symbol":"SPCE","mention_count":1,"first_mention":"2026-06-14T15:27:22.000Z","latest_mention":"2026-06-14T15:27:22.000Z","mentions_24h":0,"tweets_24h":0,"prices":[{"date":"2025-02-2